# ============================================================
# Resume Intelligence V2 — Environment Example
# ============================================================
# This project stores ALL configuration in the database.
# No .env file is required to run the app.
#
# On first run, the encryption key is auto-generated and saved
# to backend/.secret_key (gitignored). Keep that file safe.
#
# To configure the app:
#   1. Start the server:  make dev
#   2. Log in as manager/recruiter
#   3. Go to Settings and enter:
#        - OpenRouter API Key   (for LLM + embeddings)
#        - LinkedIn Username/Password (for scraping)
#        - Google Client ID/Secret   (for Google OAuth login)
#        - LinkedIn Client ID/Secret (for LinkedIn OAuth login)
#        - SMTP credentials          (for email notifications)
#
# The only reason to create a .env file is for the demo
# data loader script (scripts/load_demo_data.py), which can
# read the OpenRouter key from the env as a convenience:
#
#   OPEN_ROUTER_KEY=sk-or-v1-...
#
# Everything else is configured through the Settings UI.
# ============================================================
